Description:
LIONBRIDGE EXTERNAL POSITION TITLE

For 25 years, we have helped companies connect with their global customers and employees by delivering translation and localization solutions in 350+ languages.

Through our world-class platform, we orchestrate a network of passionate experts across the globe who partner with brands to create culturally rich experiences.

Relentless in our love of linguistics, we use the best of human and machine intelligence to forge understanding that resonates with our customers’ customers.

Based in Waltham, Massachusetts, Lionbridge maintains solution centres in 23 countries.

Lionbridge is seeking a Senior Software Developer (.Net) to support our global team. Lionbridge partners with brands to break barriers and build bridges all over the world.

Unit testing and refactoring is the norm in your day to day development activities. Educating and mentoring less skilled team members should come naturally.

Responsibilities:

Designing process automations using C# and Microsoft .NET framework and various system's APIs;
Creating and modifying code using APIs from specification, performing unit tests, fix defects;
Coordinating requirements gathering with other teams/functions;
Coordinating development work during project lifecycle;
Preparing and delivering life-cycle documents as required by project;
Good understanding of Azure and Azure components (CosmosDB, Service Bus, etc..)
Knowledge of AKS would be a plus but not mandatory.
Knowledge of Camunda would be a plus but not mandatory.
Ensuring timeliness;
Managing quality of deliverables;
Proactive - should be proactive to drive and own the tasks/deliverables
Suggesting changes to development process and driving its implementation.

 Requirements:

4 - 6 years’ experience in software development according to development standards, strong experience in C# programming;
Strong working knowledge of C# and Microsoft .NET framework (working with 8, but 6 or 7 will also be fine), .NET Core, MS SQL Server, T-SQL;
Expereince/Good understanding of Azure and Azure components (CosmosDB, Service Bus, etc..)
Ability to write technical specifications, recommendations and development documentation;
Knowledge of AKS would be a plus but not mandatory.
Knowledge of Camunda would be a plus but not mandatory.
Good knowledge of Object Oriented Design and Analysis;
Good knowledge of Entity Framework, WEB API,
Knowledge of Kubernetes and Docker;
Proactive - should be proactive to drive and own the tasks/deliverables
Very good knowledge of English, both in speech and writing;
Strong analytical and communication skills;
Ability to prioritize the workload and to work to deadlines.

We offer:

Professional development opportunities in a multi-cultural environment – Lionbridge has offices in 26 countries and many of these offices work collaboratively on projects, exposing our employees to a wide range of cultures and work styles;
Access to the latest technological solutions;
Work in a creative team and nice atmosphere;
